        -:   66:/** \geometry_module \ingroup Geometry_Module
        -:   67:  *
        -:   68:  * \returns the cross product of \c *this and \a other. This is either a scalar for size-2 vectors or a size-3 vector for size-3 vectors.
        -:   69:  *
        -:   70:  * This method is implemented for two different cases: between vectors of fixed size 2 and between vectors of fixed size 3.
        -:   71:  * 
        -:   72:  * For vectors of size 3, the output is simply the traditional cross product.
        -:   73:  *
        -:   74:  * For vectors of size 2, the output is a scalar.
        -:   75:  * Given vectors \f$ v = \begin{bmatrix} v_1 & v_2 \end{bmatrix} \f$ and \f$ w = \begin{bmatrix} w_1 & w_2 \end{bmatrix} \f$,
        -:   76:  * the result is simply \f$ v\times w = \overline{v_1 w_2 - v_2 w_1} = \text{conj}\left|\begin{smallmatrix} v_1 & w_1 \\ v_2 & w_2 \end{smallmatrix}\right| \f$;
        -:   77:  * or, to put it differently, it is the third coordinate of the cross product of \f$ \begin{bmatrix} v_1 & v_2 & v_3 \end{bmatrix} \f$ and \f$ \begin{bmatrix} w_1 & w_2 & w_3 \end{bmatrix} \f$.
        -:   78:  * For real-valued inputs, the result can be interpreted as the signed area of a parallelogram spanned by the two vectors.
        -:   79:  * 
        -:   80:  * \note With complex numbers, the cross product is implemented as
        -:   81:  * \f$ (\mathbf{a}+i\mathbf{b}) \times (\mathbf{c}+i\mathbf{d}) = (\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{c} - \mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{d}) - i(\mathbf{a} \times \mathbf{d} + \mathbf{b} \times \mathbf{c})\f$
        -:   82:  * 
        -:   83:  * \sa MatrixBase::cross3()
        -:   84:  */
        -:   85:template<typename Derived>
        -:   86:template<typename OtherDerived>
        -:   87:EIGEN_DEVICE_FUNC EIGEN_STRONG_INLINE
        -:   88:#ifndef EIGEN_PARSED_BY_DOXYGEN
        -:   89:typename internal::cross_impl<Derived, OtherDerived>::return_type
        -:   90:#else
        -:   91:inline std::conditional_t<SizeAtCompileTime==2, Scalar, PlainObject>
        -:   92:#endif
